node.text: Did Joe Biden inadvertently pay for Hunter Biden’s escapades at Chateau Marmont? Miranda Devine explains what she uncovered on Hunter’s infamous laptop.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sean Hannity on July 19, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'OLIVER NORTH ON CUBAN PROTESTS TUNE IN TONIGHT 9PM ET Hannity'.

node.text: The people of Cuba are protesting against the oppressive communist regime that has forced them to live in terrible conditions. While many prominent figures have expressed their support for the people, some radical Leftists, including Rep. AOC and Nikole Hannah-Jones, are blaming the U.S. and seem to be siding with the Cuban government. TONIGHT on “Hannity,” Lt. Col. (ret.) Oliver North will discuss the ongoing protests in Cuba and the people’s fight for freedom. Tune in at 9 PM ET or set your DVR for this must-see interview!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Sean Hannity on July 19, 2021 tagging @byrondonalds. May be an image of ‎1 person, suit and ‎text that says '‎REP. DONALDS CALLS OUT CNN: "THEY HAVE A POLITICAL AGENDA" Û مب Hannity‎'‎‎.

node.text: Rep. Byron Donalds criticized CNN host Brianna Keilar after the two had a heated exchange over election integrity legislation and Donald Trump. Rep. Donalds will join “Hannity” TONIGHT, along with Dana Loesch, to talk about media bias and CNN’s “political agenda.”

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sean Hannity on July 19, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text: President Biden has been in office for just six months, and we’ve already seen major changes to our country. TONIGHT on “Hannity,” Kayleigh McEnany and Air Fleisher will discuss the U.S. under the Biden administration. Tune in at 9 PM ET or set your DVR to never miss an episode!

node.text: The White House is pushing for MORE censorship online! Press Secretary Jen Psaki recently said that anyone banned from one social media platform should be banned from them all. Is she serious?! TONIGHT on “Hannity,” Kayleigh McEnany, Stephen Miller and Joe Concha will discuss the White House working with Big Tech. Tune in at 9 PM ET or set your DVR to never miss an episode!

node.text: Rep. Cori Bush, a member of the infamous Squad and a Defund the Police advocate, recently spent $70,000 on private security. She wants security for herself, but not for everyday Americans who rely on the police. Rep. Madison Cawthorn and Larry Elder will respond to Rep. Bush’s hypocrisy TONIGHT on “Hannity.”

node.text: The DOJ’s inspector general says that the FBI made grave errors in the handling of the case against Larry Nassar, the former physician for USA Gymnastics. Nassar was charged in 2016 after numerous athletes alleged that he sexually abused them. TONIGHT on “Hannity,” Tammy Bruce and Emily Compagno will weigh in on the FBI’s mishandling of the case.
